Synodus Anglicana, or, The constitution and proceedings of an English convocation shown from the acts and registers thereof to be agreeable to the principles of an Episcopal church. Gibson, Edmund, 1669-1748.
579 p. in various pagings.
Printed for A. and J. Churchill, London : 1672.
"Appendix. I. Three registers of the upper-house in 1562 in which the xxxix articles were agreed upon, 1640, under Archb. Laud, 1661, &c. in which the Common-prayer was revis'd. 2. The two entire journals of the lower-house in 1586 and 1588." Includes index. Some text in Latin. Reproduction of original in the Union Theological Seminary Library, New York.
